datasets.name: a5827d89
datasets.query:
SELECT 
    run_timestamp,
    warehouse_id,
    query_start_time_ms, query_end_time_ms,
    id,
    query_text,
    concurrency, 
    benchmark_catalog, 
    benchmark_schema,   
    warehouse_name,
    duration,
    duration/1000 as duration_secs,
    metrics.planning_time_ms/1000 as query_planning_time_secs,
    metrics.execution_time_ms/1000 as query_execution_time_secs,
    metrics.compilation_time_ms/1000 as query_compliation_time_secs,
    metrics.result_from_cache as result_from_cache,
    metrics.rows_produced_count as rows_produced_count,
    metrics.read_files_count as read_files_count,
    metrics.read_partitions_count as read_partitions_count,
    metrics.pruned_bytes as pruned_bytes,
    metrics.pruned_files_count as pruned_files_count,
    metrics.spill_to_disk_bytes as spill_to_disk_bytes,
    metrics.rows_read_count as rows_read_count
FROM serverless_benchmark.default._metimur_metrics_anhhoang_chu_databricks_com;

datasets.name: 17c1da0b
datasets.query:
WITH Percentiles_CTE AS (
    SELECT 
        run_timestamp, 
        id, 
        warehouse_name,
        concurrency,
        transform(
            percentile_cont(array(0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 0.90, 0.99)) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY round(duration/1000, 4)), 
            x -> round(x, 4)
        ) as Percentiles, 
        min(duration)/1000 as min_duration_secs,
        median(duration)/1000 as median_duration_secs,
        round(avg(duration)/1000,4) as avg_duration_secs,
        max(duration)/1000 as max_duration_secs,
        round(avg(metrics.planning_time_ms)/1000,4) as avg_query_planning_time_secs,
        round(avg(metrics.execution_time_ms)/100,4) as avg_query_execution_time_secs,
        round(avg(metrics.compilation_time_ms)/1000,4) as avg_query_compliation_time_secs
    FROM serverless_benchmark.default._metimur_metrics_anhhoang_chu_databricks_com
    GROUP BY run_timestamp, id, warehouse_name, concurrency
)
SELECT 
    run_timestamp, 
    id, 
    warehouse_name,
    concurrency,
    min_duration_secs,
    median_duration_secs,
    avg_duration_secs,
    max_duration_secs,
    Percentiles[0] as P25,
    Percentiles[1] as P50,
    Percentiles[2] as P75,
    Percentiles[3] as P90,
    Percentiles[4] as P99,
    avg_query_planning_time_secs,
    avg_query_execution_time_secs,
    avg_query_compliation_time_secs
FROM Percentiles_CTE
ORDER BY id

datasets.name: 1a5ed835
datasets.query:
with dbu_size_view AS
(
  SELECT '2X-Small' AS size, 4 AS dbu_per_h
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 'X-Small', 6
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 'Small', 12
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 'Medium', 24
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 'Large', 40
  UNION ALL
  SELECT 'X-Large', 80
  UNION ALL
  SELECT '2X-Large', 144
  UNION ALL
  SELECT '3X-Large', 272
  UNION ALL
  SELECT '4X-Large', 528
),

system_warehouse_cte as (
SELECT
    we.warehouse_id AS warehouse_id,
    we.event_type AS event,
    we.event_time AS event_time,
    we.cluster_count AS cluster_count,
    lead(event_time) over (PARTITION BY warehouse_id ORDER BY event_time) AS next_event_time
FROM
    system.compute.warehouse_events AS we
WHERE
    we.event_type IN (
        'STARTING', 'RUNNING', 'STOPPING', 'STOPPED',
        'SCALING_UP', 'SCALED_UP', 'SCALING_DOWN', 'SCALED_DOWN'
    )
    -- and warehouse_id = '8097a27ebcc78d0b'
)

select a. run_timestamp, a.benchmark_catalog, a.benchmark_schema, 
  a.warehouse_id, a.id, a.warehouse_name, a.warehouse_size, a.warehouse_type, a.duration as duration_ms,
  a.duration/(1000*60*60) as duration_hours, 
    CASE
    WHEN a.warehouse_type LIKE '%serverless%' THEN 0.7
    WHEN a.warehouse_type LIKE '%pro%' THEN 0.55
    WHEN a.warehouse_type LIKE '%classic%' THEN 0.22
  END AS unit_cost,
  b.cluster_count, c.dbu_per_h,
  duration_hours * cluster_count * c.dbu_per_h as dbus,
  dbus * unit_cost as dollar_dbus
from (
  select *, split_part(warehouse_name, " ", -1) as warehouse_size,
      split_part(warehouse_name, " ", -2) as warehouse_type
  from serverless_benchmark.default._metimur_metrics_anhhoang_chu_databricks_com
  ) a
join system_warehouse_cte b
join dbu_size_view c
on  a.warehouse_id = b.warehouse_id
and a.warehouse_size = c.size
and from_unixtime(a.query_start_time_ms/1000) between b.event_time and b.next_event_time
;
